comments.body:
@SteaI My bad. I thought Korean was part of the RTL issue, but it appears that it was just a typeface issue. 

I think the default typefaces do not actually have any Korean characters, thus it will draw blocks. The correct way to find a typeface on the device is to use the `SKFontManager`:

```csharp
// find a typeface that has the characters
var tf = SKFontManager.Default.MatchCharacter('헬');

// create a paint
var paint = new SKPaint { Typeface = tf };

// draw the text
canvas.DrawText("헬로우 월드", ...);
```
